Subject:    negative caching in bind
From:       <a href="?a=95837786000001&r=1&w=2">Mark Crispin &lt;mrc () SUMEX-AIM ! Stanford ! EDU&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198910">1989-10-15 19:48:31</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627050&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627050&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Well, some domain resolvers which have negative caching have been having
problems with servers which are authoritatively rejecting names that are
perfectly valid.  Once in the resolver's cache, you have to wait until the
negative cache entry times out (or if some resolver client insists that the
resolver go out and ask again) before you can reference that name again...

